{"key":"processedPost-16137420","value":{"id":16137420,"first":16137106,"last":27735074,"when":1335369289,"utime":"04/25/12 06:54 PM","content":"Fruits from some strains are barely attached to the substrate and as A.S. said they tend to fall over.&nbsp; With these, go ahead and twist them off.&nbsp;  <br /><br />Other strains form individuals and clusters that are firmly attached to the substrate mass, and if you twist-and-pull it will leave a large divot.&nbsp; When you have fruits like these(which are more common) they should be cut off.<br /><br />Let's not repeat the myth that the leftover stem butts rot.&nbsp; They don't.<br />RR","title":"Re: How do you deal with substrate on the shroom base after harvesting?"}}